==English==

===Noun===
'''profilometry'''

# use of a [[technique]] in the measurement and [[profiling]] of an object.

'''profilometry''', eddy current

# [[methodology]] of performing [[eddy current]] [[profiling]] of tubing.
#:''The profilometry of the tubing was cunducted directly following the eddy current exam.''

'''profilometry''', surface

# [[technique]] in which a diamond [[stylus]], in contact with a sample, measures surface [[variations]] as a function of position.
# use of a [[laser]] or white-light, computer-generated projections to perform surface measurements of three dimensional objects.
#:''Surface profilometry was used to measure the film thickness.''

